du n no y. . . na jaane kyon ( english : do n't know why ) is a 2010 bilingual indian film . it was directed by sanjay sharma and written by his brother kapil sharma who also played the lead . it premiered in april 2010 at india 's first mainstream gay film festival , the kashish mumbai international queer film festival . it features the first gay kiss in indian cinema between &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; parashar and kapil sharma . the film had its north american premiere at the i view film festival in new york city and was screened at the sydney film festival , the indian film festival of london ( &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ) and filmfest &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; in germany . du n no y. . . na jaane kyon was released in theatres in austria , italy and switzerland in september 2010 . the film received the best sensitive award at the kashish queer international film festival 2010 and the viewer choice award at the &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; film festival of sydney 2010 . it also won the best film awards at poland film festival 2014 , &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; italy 2014 , and the &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; international film festival 2014 . lead actors &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; parashar and kapil sharma won best actor awards at out view film festival greece 2012 . the film got screened at 17 international film festivals . a sequel has also been made starring zeenat aman , kapil sharma and &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; parashar .